-- Pimco appoints four deputy chief investment officers
-- By Sam Forgione
-- Wed Jan 29, 2014 09:24AM EST
-- None



NEW YORK, Jan 29 (Reuters) - Bond giant Pimco said on Wednesday it had appointed four additional deputy chief investment officers, while two portfolio managers have departed.

Mark Kiesel, Virginie Maisonneuve, Scott Mather and Mihir Worah, currently managing directors at the firm, have been appointed deputy chief investment officers. Pimco also said that managing directors Charles Lahr and Marc Seidner will leave, while Sudi Mariappa will re-join as a managing director and generalist portfolio manager.